Section C
:SKRSLUT.
.sp 3mm
EVENT CANCELLATION INSURANCE
.sp 5mm
:FED.
1.0 Whom does the insurance cover?
:SKRSLUT.
:SWISS8.
.sp 3mm
The holder of a valid and active MasterCard Silver card issued by
&BANKNAVN..
.sp 5mm
.kp off
.kp on
:SWISS10.
:FED.
2.0 What does the insurance cover?
.sp 3mm
:SWISS8.
:FED.
2.1 Coverage
:SKRSLUT.
.br
The insurance covers purchases of tickets all over the world The
insurance applies from the time when the cardholder purchases the
ticket(s) and pays for them in full with his/her card.
.br
The insurance covers the purchase of tickets to a minimum price of DKK
200 each (excluding any fees or charges), that the cardholder has paid
for in full with his/her card.
.kp off
.kp on
.sp 3mm
The insurance covers up to five tickets per event. The maximum
compensation payable is DKK 2,000 per ticket and DKK 10,000 per year.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
2.1.1 If the policy holder cancels his/her card, or if the
insurance coverage ceases on account of the working relationship
between &BANKNAVn. and the insurer being terminated or similar,
tickets purchased using the card before the expiry of the agreement
will still be covered in accordance with the present insurance
terms and conditions, up to the date of the event.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
2.1.2 Insured tickets:
.br
Tickets for personal use for events such as concerts, theatrical
performances, sports events, amusement parks and the like, with a
minimum nominal value of DKK 200 each, which have been paid for in
full using the card during the insurance period.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
2.1.3 The coverage does not apply to tickets of the following types:
.br
.of 5mm
*¤Cinema tickets
.of
.of 5mm
*¤Museum tickets
.of
.of 5mm
*¤Season tickets of any kind
.kp off
.kp on
.of 5mm
*¤Ski lift passes
.kp off
.kp on
.of 5mm
*¤Annual subscriptions
.kp off
.kp on
.of 5mm
*¤Travel tickets
.of
.of 5mm
*¤Tickets purchased for the purpose of resale
.of
.sp 5mm
.kp off
.kp on
:SWISS10.
:FED.
3.0 Compensation
:SKRSLUT.
:SWISS8.
.sp 3mm
Under the insurance, compensation will be paid in the amount of the
nominal value of the ticket in the event that the ticket(s) have to be
cancelled or cannot be used if one of the events listed below affects
the insured or his/her immediate family in the Nordic region:
.sp 3mm
.of 5mm
*¤Death
.of
.of 5mm
*¤Acute illness or unexpected and acute deterioration of a chronic illness
.of
.of 5mm
*¤Acute injury
.kp off
.kp on
.of 5mm
*¤Damage to the insured's home, business or office, that occurred after
the tickets were paid for and which requires his/her presence
.kp off
.kp on
.of 5mm
*¤Requirement to perform military service or jury duty, which cannot be
altered
.kp off
.kp on
.of 5mm
*¤ID card stolen up to 48 hours prior to the event, where the ID card in
question is the only valid identification
.kp off
.kp on
.of 5mm
*¤Acute damage to or theft of a vehicle up to 48 hours before the event
which makes transport to the event impossible
.kp off
.kp on
.of 5mm
*¤Delay to public transport lasting at least four hours, which results in
the insured being unable to travel to the event
.of
.of 5mm
*¤Collision/accident en route to the event, which requires towing of the
vehicle when the insured is using a private vehicle to travel to the event.
.of
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
Immediate family: In this context, 'immediate family' is taken to
refer to the insured's partner/life partner/spouse, children
(including adoptive children), children-in-law, grandchildren, step
children, step-children-in-law, parents, parents-in-law, grandparents,
step-parents, step-parents-in-law, siblings, brothers and
sisters-in-law.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
:FED.
3.1 Exceptions
:SKRSLUT.
.br
The insurance does not cover cancellation resulting from:
.sp 3mm
.of 5mm
*¤Treatment/operation/health cure or similar that was planned or could
have been foreseen/expected before the tickets were purchased.
.of
.of 5mm
*¤Any illness/condition that the insured was aware of and which
constituted a significant risk that it would not be possible to attend
the event.
.kp off
.kp on
.of 5mm
*¤Pregnancy. However, the insurance does cover cancellation as a
result of a sudden medical condition/complications that prevent the
insured from attending the event.
.kp off
.kp on
.of 5mm
*¤Any psychological condition diagnosed before the tickets were purchased.
.kp off
.kp on
.of 5mm
*¤Abuse of intoxicants or narcotics.
.kp off
.kp on
.of 5mm
*¤Participation in criminal activities.
.kp off
.kp on
.of 5mm
*¤Cancellation of the event.
.of
.of 5mm
*¤War, civil unrest, revolt, revolution, acts of terrorism, force
majeure or nuclear reaction.
.of
.sp 5mm
.kp off
.kp on
:SWISS10.
:FED.
4.0 Reporting claims
:SKRSLUT.
.sp 3mm
:SWISS8.
Any and all claims must be reported without undue delay to
Forsikringsrådgiverne on +45 70 27 03 04, on weekdays between 09.00 and
16.00. You can print a claims report form from
:US.www.forsikringsraadgiverne.dk.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
When submitting a claim, the insured is to present the following
documentation:
.sp 3mm
.of 5mm
*¤A claim report, completed and signed. In the event of theft, the
incident must be reported to the police in situ, and confirmation of the
report to the police is to be submitted together with the claim report.
.of
.of 5mm
*¤Original purchase receipt, together with an account statement that
documents the date of purchase and price.
.kp off
.kp on
.of 5mm
*¤In the case of acute illness or accident, a doctor's note must be
enclosed, in which the doctor confirms that attendance at the event is
impossible.
.kp off
.kp on
.of 5mm
*¤In the event of damage to home/business/office, this must be documented
in writing.
.kp off
.kp on
.of 5mm
*¤In the event of a stolen ID card, documentation must be provided in the
form of a police report.
.kp off
.kp on
.of 5mm
*¤In the event or requirement to report for military service or jury
duty, written documentation of same must be provided.
.kp off
.kp on
.of 5mm
*¤In the event of accident involving or theft of a vehicle, written
documentation of same must be provided
.kp off
.kp on
.of 5mm
*¤In the event of delays to public transport, written documentation of the
delay must be provided.
.of
.of 5mm
*¤Any other document the insurer considers necessary to approve the claim
and the associated compensation.
.of
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
If the insured can raise a claim against a third party, CHARTIS
shall enter into the claim in place of the insured and may raise
the claim against said third party.
.sp 3mm
Otherwise, refer to the SHARED TERMS AND CONDITIONS, SECTION A
.sp 3mm
It is the Danish version of the applicable regulations/provisions that
apply at any and all times.
.sp 5mm
